m_q.target_metric: Count of days in 2024 where at least one sampling point at Constitution Beach had Enterococcus count < 104 and at least one other sampling point had Enterococcus count ≥ 104
sub_questions: How to interpret '<' symbol in Enterococcus columns?
How to handle missing values in Enterococcus columns?
Are all three sampling points (Enterococcus, Enterococcus.1, Enterococcus.2) always present for each date?
How to parse 'Date' column from string format 'Month Day, Year'?

schema_conflicts: Duplicate column names: 'Tag', 'Tag.1', 'Tag.2' and 'Enterococcus', 'Enterococcus.1', 'Enterococcus.2' suggest multiple sampling points
Date column stored as object/string instead of datetime

scale_issues: Enterococcus values appear as floats but may represent discrete counts
Rain columns have very small values (0.0-0.89) suggesting possible unit conversion needed

format_notes: Date values are quoted strings with format 'Month Day, Year'
Tag columns contain '<' symbol indicating values below detection limit
Some Enterococcus values have commas in sample data (e.g., 789.0, 727.0, 226.0)
Missing values appear as empty strings in Tag columns

constraints: Date must be parseable to valid dates in 2024
Each row represents one day with up to 3 sampling points
derived_filters: Exclude rows where all Enterococcus values are missing
Interpret '<' in Tag columns as values below detection limit (use corresponding Enterococcus value)
statistical_tests: Validate that Enterococcus values <104 when corresponding Tag is '<'
output_format_requirements: Must handle partial data (some sampling points missing)
